The paper discusses a type of artificial neural network architecture called Echo State Networks (ESN) which are commonly used for time series processing and learning. This falls under the category of neural networks and machine learning, which is covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. The use of a reservoir of product nodes for time series computation is a novel approach and may be of interest to researchers in the field of neural networks and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Other likely sub-categories include cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.IT (Information Theory), as these sub-categories also cover topics related to neural networks and machine learning.
